Defendant Nicholas J Morgano in court with attorney Michael S Holzman.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence

3 Years 6 months Imprisonment (Credit - 0 days )
- 1 Year 6 months of Initial Confinement
- 2 Years of Extended Supervision


Term of Probation: 3 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- Follow through with AODA Assessmentthat was completed through the Sober America Program and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- letter of apology to Wrico Stamping;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided and pay surcharge;
- No contact with co-actors, Wrico Stamping, Employees at Wrico Stamping.

Restitution: $406.00 to Wrico Stamping Company joint and several with co-defendants, $6,610.69 to Wrico Stamping (to be paid at the rate of $182.00 per month commencing 8-1-14)

Costs: $268.00 
DNA Surcharge: $250.00
(To to be paid as a condition of probation ).

Condition Time:  120 days Huber NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - Last 60 days stayed to be used at the agent's discretion.  Defendant to report to Huber by noon on 5-2-14.

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.
